# Semantic Design Tokens — Primitives vs Semantic Variables

## Purpose

Every style property in component files **must** use **semantic** design tokens. Never use hard-coded color/size values or references to **primitive** CSS variables. Semantic tokens carry intent (e.g. "default background", "brand border") while primitives are raw values (e.g. "brand dark 50", "size 16") that may change without notice.

This rule applies to **CSS Modules** (`.module.css`), **SCSS** (`.scss`), and **TypeScript** files that contain inline styles or CSS-in-JS patterns.

---

## What to detect

### A. Hard-coded primitive values

Flag any of the following when used as style values:

| Pattern                    | Examples                                         |
| -------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| Hex colors                 | `#fff`, `#ffffff`, `#006dcc`, `#27292a`          |
| RGB / RGBA                 | `rgb(0, 109, 204)`, `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5)`   |
| HSL / HSLA                 | `hsl(207, 100%, 40%)`, `hsla(0, 0%, 100%, 0.8)`  |
| Raw px for spacing         | `padding: 16px`, `margin: 8px 24px`, `gap: 12px` |
| Raw px for border-radius   | `border-radius: 8px`                             |
| Raw px for font-size       | `font-size: 14px`                                |
| Raw px for line-height     | `line-height: 24px`                              |
| Raw px for icon dimensions | `width: 24px; height: 24px` (on icon wrappers)   |

### B. Primitive CSS variable references

Flag `var()` calls that reference variables from the **primitive** `:root` block in `design-system-tokens.css`:

| Primitive prefix           | Examples                                               |
| -------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| `--size-*`                 | `var(--size-4)`, `var(--size-16)`, `var(--size-24)`    |
| `--brand-light-*`          | `var(--brand-light-10)`, `var(--brand-light-20)`       |
| `--brand-dark-*`           | `var(--brand-dark-50)`, `var(--brand-dark-60)`         |
| `--neutrals-*`             | `var(--neutrals-white-00)`, `var(--neutrals-black-80)` |
| `--system-error-*`         | `var(--system-error-10)`, `var(--system-error-50)`     |
| `--system-success-*`       | `var(--system-success-10)`, `var(--system-success-50)` |
| `--system-warning-*`       | `var(--system-warning-10)`, `var(--system-warning-50)` |
| `--system-info-*`          | `var(--system-info-10)`, `var(--system-info-50)`       |
| `--interactivity-states-*` | `var(--interactivity-states-default)`                  |
| `--gradients-*`            | `var(--gradients-gradient-1-stop-1)`                   |

> **Note:** `--font-family-*` and `--font-weight-*` exist in both the primitive and semantic blocks. Always use the **semantic** versions (`--font-family-heading`, `--font-family-body`, `--font-family-small-details`, `--font-weight-strong`, `--font-weight-default`).

