## Examples

### CSS Modules (`.module.css`)

**Bad — hard-coded values:**

```css
.root {
  background: #ffffff;
  color: #27292a;
  padding: 16px;
  border-radius: 8px;
  border: 1px solid #dee1e3;
  font-size: 14px;
  line-height: 20px;
}

.icon {
  width: 24px;
  height: 24px;
}
```

**Good — semantic tokens:**

```css
.root {
  background: var(--color-background-default);
  color: var(--color-text-default);
  padding: var(--spacing-m);
  border-radius: var(--corner-radius-s);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-weaker);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body-s);
  line-height: var(--line-height-body-s);
}

.icon {
  width: var(--icon-size-m);
  height: var(--icon-size-m);
}
```

---

**Bad — primitive variable references:**

```css
.card {
  background: var(--neutrals-white-00);
  color: var(--neutrals-black-80);
  padding: var(--size-16);
  border-radius: var(--size-8);
  border-color: var(--brand-dark-50);
  gap: var(--size-8);
}

.card:hover {
  border-color: var(--interactivity-states-hover);
}

.errorMessage {
  color: var(--system-error-100);
  background: var(--system-error-10);
}
```

**Good — semantic tokens:**

```css
.card {
  background: var(--color-background-default);
  color: var(--color-text-default);
  padding: var(--spacing-m);
  border-radius: var(--corner-radius-s);
  border-color: var(--color-border-brand);
  gap: var(--spacing-xs);
}

.card:hover {
  border-color: var(--color-border-interactivity-hover);
}

.errorMessage {
  color: var(--color-text-system-error);
  background: var(--color-fill-system-error-weak);
}
```

---

### SCSS files (`.scss`)

**Bad:**

```scss
.wrapper {
  padding: 24px;
  background-color: #f3f5f6;

  .title {
    font-size: 32px;
    line-height: 40px;
    color: #006dcc;
  }
}
```

**Good:**

```scss
.wrapper {
  padding: var(--spacing-l);
  background-color: var(--color-background-weakest);

  .title {
    font-size: var(--font-size-titles-xl);
    line-height: var(--line-height-titles-xl);
    color: var(--color-text-brand);
  }
}
```

---

### TypeScript inline styles / CSS-in-JS

**Bad:**

```tsx
<div style={{ padding: '16px', color: '#27292a', backgroundColor: '#ffffff' }}>
  Content
</div>
```

**Good:**

```tsx
<div
  style={{
    padding: 'var(--spacing-m)',
    color: 'var(--color-text-default)',
    backgroundColor: 'var(--color-background-default)',
  }}
>
  Content
</div>
```

---

### Shorthand properties

**Bad:**

```css
.box {
  border: 1px solid #b5b8ba;
  padding: 8px 16px;
  margin: 0 24px 16px;
}
```

**Good:**

```css
.box {
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-weak);
  padding: var(--spacing-xs) var(--spacing-m);
  margin: 0 var(--spacing-l) var(--spacing-m);
}
```

---

### Component-scoped CSS variables (`--cv-*`)

Component variables should reference semantic tokens, not primitives:

**Bad:**

```css
.root {
  --cv-card-bg: var(--neutrals-white-00);
  --cv-card-border: var(--brand-dark-50);
  --cv-card-padding: var(--size-16);
}
```

**Good:**

```css
.root {
  --cv-card-bg: var(--color-background-default);
  --cv-card-border: var(--color-border-brand);
  --cv-card-padding: var(--spacing-m);
}
```

---

## Exceptions (where primitives are allowed)

The following cases are **not** violations:

| Case                                 | Rationale                                               | Example                                       |
| ------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| `0` / `0px`                          | Zero needs no token                                     | `margin: 0`, `padding: 0px`                   |
| `1px` in borders                     | No spacing token for 1px                                | `border: 1px solid var(...)`                  |
| `2px` in outlines                    | No spacing token for 2px                                | `outline: 2px solid var(...)`                 |
| CSS keywords                         | Not tokenizable                                         | `auto`, `inherit`, `initial`, `unset`, `none` |
| Percentages                          | Layout-specific                                         | `width: 100%`, `top: 50%`                     |
| Viewport units                       | Layout-specific                                         | `100vh`, `100vw`, `100dvh`                    |
| Opacity values                       | Numeric 0–1                                             | `opacity: 0.5`                                |
| Z-index values                       | Stacking integers                                       | `z-index: 10`                                 |
| Transition / animation               | Durations and easings                                   | `transition: 0.2s ease`, `300ms`              |
| `var()` fallbacks                    | Hard-coded fallback inside `var()` is acceptable        | `var(--color-text-default, #27292a)`          |
| `calc()` with tokens                 | Arithmetic on semantic tokens is fine                   | `calc(var(--spacing-m) + var(--spacing-xs))`  |
| `design-system-tokens.css`           | Auto-generated file; do not modify                      | Entire file is excluded                       |
| `tokens.css`                         | Manual breakpoint tokens (`--bp-*`)                     | `--bp-sm: 768px`                              |
| SVG attributes                       | `viewBox`, `d`, `points`, etc.                          | `viewBox="0 0 24 24"`                         |
| Media queries with `--bp-*`          | Breakpoint tokens are not design tokens                 | `@media (min-width: 768px)`                   |
| `max-width` / `min-width` on layouts | Container constraints without a design token equivalent | `max-width: 1200px`                           |

